{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_217","type":"agent_message","text":"I reproduced `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.springframework.boot:spring-boot:4.0.6` with the required GraalVM only, after confirming `native-image --version` matched `25.0.3 2026-04-21`, and `latest_graalvm_home` resolves to the same real installation the build used. The metadata file is valid JSON and remains modified at [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/7690-3a6d7601/metadata/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.6/reachability-metadata.json).\n\nThe remaining failures are still 6, and they do not appear fixable with reachability metadata alone:\n- `BeanDefinitionLoaderTest`, `ClearCachesApplicationListenerTest`, `EnvironmentConverterTest`: `EnvironmentPostProcessorApplicationListener` is required for `SpringFactoriesLoader`, but once present Boot 4.0.6 asserts `mainApplicationClass not found` in native mode for `SpringApplication` usages without a `main` frame.\n- `SpringApplicationAotProcessorTest` x2: inside a native image, Boot always requires generated AOT initializers during `SpringApplication.run(...)`, so `SpringApplicationAotProcessor` trips `AotInitializerNotFoundException` before it can generate them.\n- `ProcessInfoTest`: `new ProcessInfo().getVirtualThreads()` still returns `null`; this looks tied to native-image monitoring/JMX support rather than missing reflection entries.\n\nI also tried an additional metadata-only experiment around Spring AOT resources and reverted it because it had no effect. If you want, I can continue with broader-scope fixes outside metadata-only constraints, most likely in the test fixture or native-image configuration."}}
